tip.text: Adorable cafe ruined by one of the worst flat whites I've ever had. Coffee is rubbish, but a fine place to work.
Awesome sandwiches and service. Free WiFi and decent coffee too, this is one of the best places for cheap breakfast or sandwiches in the area.
Flat whites are large here but they are pretty good.
Amazing zoo, full of excellent areas for animals. Check out the feeding times for tigers!
Really great bartender and cocktails, with great jazz and a chill interior. Awesome spot in Basel.
Gorgeous, huge park you can spend half a day in just wandering. The mini golf is cute!
Absolutely AMAZING food and wine selection for a great price. Coffee is good and wait staff ate friendly, helpful, and efficient.
It's a resort, but as they go it's not bad. The breakfast buffet is nice, the restaurant is hit/miss with food, but the beach and pool are awesome. Avoid the cocktails, they're hilariously brutal.
This place saves Bohol from otherwise terrible coffee and food. They are amazing, try everything.
One of the best joints for cocktails in Ubud, it's posh here but worth it. The food is also killer. They take credit cards, which is handy; your bill is likely to be over 500,000IDR for two.
Phenomenal coffee, from espresso to lattes. The atmosphere is cute but the wifi is a bit spotty. Still, the coffee is very, very good. Some of the best in Ubud.
Awesome selection of local beers on tap and a wide range of bottles from around the world. Worth checking out!
A lovely glass espresso machine and fantastic coffee, check this place out before you explore the river or nearby restaurants.
Simple but tasty shisha selection and amazing tea and coffee. Decor is lovely and it's relaxed yet lively.
Delicious coffee, friendly and fast staff, with a lovely terrace to sit outside on during the summer months. The interior is large and cozy at the same time. 👍
It's as many locals as expats in here, and the beer and food is crap. Makes me sad to think this is how Canada is served to many Brits 😢
You'll get a fantastic coffee here.
The Mac and Cheese is delicious and the baristas will make you coffee after coffee that you'll love.
Presented without cynicism or camp, this place is actually an amazing and interesting museum. Very fun. While small, it's well worth it.
Plainly: you need to drink here. Joey Donnelly is one of the best bartenders in Canada, and the rest of the staff steps up to kick just as much ass.
Beer selection is okay and prices are decent. Cute atmosphere and friendly vibe. Nothing too special but sort of adorable.
Very, very good noodles (my favourite is the egg noodles) with delicious toppings and sauces. Open late and definitely worth a visit.
Fun rum-based drinks for cheap. Relaxed atmosphere and okay beers on tap as well.

Awesome beers (many very hoppy American IPAs, black IPAs, and stouts on when I was there) for crazy cheap (often £2 for 0.5l). Quiet and chill atmosphere, a hidden gem surrounded by crazy night clubs.
Delicious potato pancakes, really good herring, and some of the best pierogies I've had in Warsaw. Pierogies are traditionally boiled, so good. The Bulgarian wine is delicious too!
Friendly bartenders who make good cocktails. A relaxed atmosphere during the week, great place to hang out.
£12.50 to get in, but gorgeous vires, amazing Castle apartments, and hours of walking about. Go on a sunny day and be amazed!
Don't get hustled if you're a farang; matches should run you 2,000 Baht for ringside tickets. Don't pay any of the touts farther from the gates offering higher ticket prices!
